From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Shawn Hoffman <business@symbrkrs.com>
Date: Thu, 7 May 2026 15:49:46 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] 9163: Hexagon: fix disasm/semantic bugs, increase decode
 coverage, add tests

hexagon: fix rol pcode to compute true rotate

The rol* constructors were emitting (rs << N) | zext(rs s< 0) which only
folds the sign bit into bit 0 instead of rotating the high bits back into
the low.  Use the standard (x << N) | (x >> (W - N)) pattern so the
single-shot, accumulating, and bitwise variants all match the ISA.

hexagon: prefix !cmp.eq/gt/gtu rather than suffix

LLVM disassembles the negated cmp constructors as "!cmp.eq Pd, Rs, Rt"
not "cmp.eq! Pd, Rs, Rt".  Quote the bang into the head token so the
display matches; pcode is unchanged.

hexagon: fix M2_mpyu_*_s1 typo squaring Rs instead of Rs*Rt

Both the plain and accumulating M2_mpyu :<<1 forms had zext(Rs)*zext(Rs).
Multiply by Rt as the encoding intends.

hexagon: drop spurious Rd5 from ictagw match list

ictagw has no destination register; Rd5 was listed in the constructor's
operand expression but never used.  Remove it so the constructor only
binds the operands it actually consumes.

hexagon: swap min/minu operand display to match LLVM

LLVM prints min as "min(Rt, Rs)" not "min(Rs, Rt)".  Reorder the
display tokens for the four scalar/pair min and minu constructors;
pcode already evaluates min(rt, rs).

hexagon: add V62 A6_vminub_RdP decode-only stub

Adds the paired-output vminub form that produces both Rdd and Pe; bodied
as unimpl since we don't model the multi-write semantics yet.

hexagon: add V62 vtrunehb/vtrunohb _ppp decode-only stubs

The pair-pair forms S6_vtrunehb_ppp / S6_vtrunohb_ppp share the existing
vtrunehb/vtrunohb mnemonics but use op2127=0x0c with op0507=3/5; add them
alongside the existing v8 forms.

hexagon: drop buggy icdataw decoder using icinva encoding

hexagon: add V66 icdataw and memcpy decode-only stubs

Y2_icdataw uses Inst{31-21}=0b01010101110 in HexagonDepInstrInfo.td
which is op2127=0x2e with op13=1.  L6_memcpy is greenfield.

hexagon: add V68 dmlink/dmpause/dmpoll/dmresume/dmstart/dmwait stubs

DMA descriptor-list controls from V68; all six are decode-only (no pcode
model) and slot in next to dmsyncht using the documented Y6_dm* encodings
from HexagonDepInstrInfo.td.

hexagon: add V68 memw_aq decode-only stub

Acquire-load form L2_loadw_aq from V68; same iclass/op2127 family as the
existing memw_phys constructor but distinguished by op0513=0x40.

hexagon: add V81 Y2_tlbpp decode-only stub

V81 paired-source tlbp - shares the tlbp mnemonic with the v2 form but
takes Rss and uses op2127=0x63.

hexagon_hvx: add FP, BF16, F8 and ZReg operand classes

Adds .sf/.bf/.f8/.x lane-suffix operand classes used by the IEEE-FP, BF16
and FP8 stub families (V68/V73/V79), the .ub Rtt suffix used by V65
vrmpy_rtt, and the V66 ZReg quad-vector classes (Vdddd / Vyyyy) plus
Rt8/Rx8 byte-subregister selectors for the matrix-multiply family.

hexagon_hvx: tighten vassign bit constraints

Replace the open-ended op21/op1617 patterns on the existing vassign and
Vsf/Vhf-from-qf32/qf16 constructors with the full op2123/op1620 fields,
matching the LLVM encodings exactly so neighbouring stubs don't decode
ambiguously.

hexagon_hvx: rename Qx accumulating vcmp.eq/gt mnemonics

The nine vcmp_eqand_/vcmp_gtand_ constructors were displaying as plain
"vcmp.eq Qd, ..." which collides with the non-accumulating vcmp form.
Append &= via the head-token suffix so the disassembly reads
"vcmp.eq&= Qx, Vu, Vv" matching LLVM's V6_vcmp_*_and class.

hexagon_hvx: add vhist/vhistq decode-only stubs

Closes the long-standing silent vhist mis-decode.  Both V6_vhist (no
operands) and V6_vhistq (predicated by Qv4) match the documented
Inst{31-16}=0x1E00, Inst{13-0}=0x2080 pattern.  Also lays down the
section header that following commits will append decode-only stubs
under.

hexagon_hvx: add V60 paired vmpy hus/hv/hvsrs decode stubs

V6_vmpyhus, V6_vmpyhv and V6_vmpyhvsrs plus their _acc variants - five
new stubs for the V60 paired-output multiplies that the existing scalar
vmpy constructors don't cover.

hexagon_hvx: add V65 vrmpy{bub,ub}_rtt decode stubs

V6_vrmpybub_rtt and V6_vrmpyub_rtt with their _acc partners - the V65
forms that take a paired Rtt scalar source instead of a vector Vv.

hexagon_hvx: add V68 IEEE-FP decode stub family

Eleven stubs for the V68 IEEE half/single-precision family:
vfmax/vfmin .hf and .sf, vmpy_hf_hf and the qf-accumulating variants,
vabs_hf, vadd_hf_hf and vdmpy_sf_hf_acc.  All decode-only.

hexagon_hvx: add V73 BF16 decode stub family

Eleven stubs for V73 bfloat16 - vadd/vsub/vmpy_sf_bf, vcvt_bf_sf,
vmax/vmin_bf and the four vgtbf qfloat-accumulating predicate forms.

hexagon_hvx: add V79 FP8 and qfext decode stubs

Nine stubs for V79: vabs/vfneg_f8, vfmax/vfmin_f8, vcvt2 to .b/.ub from
.hf, plus the three qfext getters/setters (V6_get_qfext, _oracc, set).

hexagon_hvx: add V81 qfloat vcmp.eq and valign4 stubs

Six veqhf/veqsf qfloat-accumulating predicate forms (and/or/xor for both
.hf and .sf) plus V6_valign4.

hexagon_hvx: add V66 ZReg matrix decode stub family

Greenfield decode coverage for the V66 ZReg matrix-multiply unit: 20
vrmpyz multiplier variants spanning vr16mpyz/vr8mpyzs and the four .c/.n
lane shapes, V6_zextract, plus six z-loads (V6_zLd_ai/_pi/_ppu and the
predicated counterparts).  All bodies unimpl - no matrix pcode emitted.

Hexagon: add stub- and packet-coverage regression-pin tests

Two new JUnit tests pin the disassembly text emitted for representative
encodings of the recently added decoder stubs (HexagonStubCoverageTest)
and packet-context decoding (HexagonPacketCoverageTest), so a future edit
that accidentally drops or shadows a constructor will surface as a
deliberate review point rather than a silent regression.

hexagon: drop redundant togglebit shift-count guard

hexagon: model sxt7 shift amount in register-form shifts

hexagon: refresh comments to reflect current support

hexagon_float: build sfmake/dfmake from bit pattern per V73

hexagon: drop stale TODOs that no longer apply

Hexagon: expand tests for shift edge cases and recent fixes
